# Platform Profile: Gemini

**Provider:** Google DeepMind  
**Current Flagship:** Gemini 3.1 Pro / Ultra  
**Interface:** gemini.google.com, Google Workspace (Docs, Sheets, Gmail, Drive), API

---

## Strengths
- Leads reasoning benchmarks among frontier models (Gemini 3.1 Pro)
- 2M token context window — largest of any mainstream platform
- Native multimodal: video, audio, images, and text in a single session
- Deep Google Workspace integration — reads and writes Docs, Sheets, Slides, Gmail, Drive natively
- Google ecosystem orchestration — can chain across Calendar, Meet, Search
- Strong for data analysis tasks involving large document sets
- Fast inference at high context lengths via Flash models
- Multilingual capability across a broad language set

## Weaknesses
- Prose quality and instruction-following below Claude for complex structured tasks
- Less precise at nuanced, multi-constraint instructions than Claude or ChatGPT
- Google Workspace integration is its primary differentiator — less compelling outside that ecosystem
- Gemini Advanced (consumer) has more limited agent capabilities than API

## Context Window
- Gemini 3.1 Pro/Ultra: 2M tokens
- Gemini Flash: 1M tokens
- Behavior: Strongest large-context performance of any platform; handles million-token inputs with good recall

## Memory & Persistence
- **Gems:** Custom AI personas with persistent instructions (consumer equivalent of GPTs)
- **Google Workspace:** Work history and files persist naturally via Drive
- **No cross-session chat memory** by default outside Workspace context
- **Handoff note:** For Workspace-integrated work, Gemini picks up context from Drive files automatically — reference the file, don't re-paste the content

## System Prompt Support
- ✅ Full system prompt support via API
- ✅ Gems (custom instructions) persist across sessions in Gemini Advanced
- System instructions are respected but less robustly than Claude for highly detailed constraints

## Tool Availability
- Google Search (native, real-time)
- Google Workspace (Docs, Sheets, Slides, Gmail, Drive, Calendar — native)
- Code execution (Python)
- Image, video, and audio understanding
- YouTube video analysis (native)
- API extensions and function calling

## Prompt Format Conventions
- Responds well to direct conversational prompts
- Benefits from explicit role definition at the start
- For Workspace tasks: reference files by name/link rather than pasting content
- For large context tasks: structure the document set clearly; Gemini handles bulk well
- Less dependent on XML-style structured prompts than Claude

## Ideal Task Types
- Massive document analysis (legal discovery, research corpora, large codebases)
- Google Workspace automation (summarize inbox, update Sheet, draft in Docs)
- Multimodal tasks involving video or audio
- Research tasks requiring live Google Search integration
- Tasks where 2M context enables analysis that other platforms can't fit
- International/multilingual work
- Reasoning-intensive tasks where benchmark performance matters

